profile_positions.description:
During my time as lead project manager for Iles de Paix's sustainable development education programme, I have successfully spearheaded and secured the programme from its inception in 2018 by writing yearly funding proposals and reports (with all the nuances of PMEL) and implementing all programme activities. In the end, I can proudly claim the following achievements as my own:

- Reaching over 4500 youth by singlehandedly elaborating and holding ESD workshops on various global topics (sustainable food systems and consumption, climate change, gender equality, poverty cycles, etc.) and establishing close relations with over 30 schools and youth organisations;
- Translating and adapting 8 learning tools (booklets, short films, calendars, etc.) for classroom use from French or English to German or Luxembourgish and delivering over 1500 tools to partner schools;
- Organizing and co-organizing 10 awareness-raising events (film screenings, youth festivals, teacher conventions, outdoor events, etc.), performing radio interviews, moderating debates, translating press releases and participating in video campaigns;
- Planning and executing a two week field mission to Tanzania (Arusha, Karatu) establishing a 2 year cultural exchange project between Luxembourgish and Tanzanian students;
- Establishing Iles de Paix Luxembourg as a known and appreciated actor in the national sustainable development education and awareness-raising sector.
- Maintained and fostered close working relations with various NGOs nationally and internationally, particularly with Iles de Paix Belgium.

"It has been a pleasure working with you; a pleasure shared by the team from which I only ever heard praise about your professionalism, concern to do well and your team spirit!" - Marie W., Director of IDP Belgium
